# Development Workflow

EasyEditor uses modern development tools and workflows to ensure code quality and maintainability.

## Prerequisites
- Node.js >= 18.0.0
- pnpm >= 9.12.2

## Getting Started
Clone the repository and install dependencies:
```bash
git clone git@github.com:Easy-Editor/EasyEditor.git
cd EasyEditor
pnpm install
```

## Development Commands
- `pnpm dev`: Run development server for all packages
- `pnpm build`: Build all packages
- `pnpm types`: Generate TypeScript types
- `pnpm test`: Run tests
- `pnpm example:dashboard`: Run the dashboard example

## Monorepo Structure
EasyEditor uses pnpm workspaces for monorepo management:
- [pnpm-workspace.yaml](mdc:pnpm-workspace.yaml): Workspace configuration
- [turbo.json](mdc:turbo.json): Turborepo configuration for build pipelines

## Release Process
EasyEditor uses Changesets for versioning and publishing:
- `pnpm pub:changeset`: Create a new changeset
- `pnpm pub:version`: Update versions based on changesets
- `pnpm pub:release`: Publish packages to npm

## Code Quality
- [biome.json](mdc:biome.json): Biome configuration for linting and formatting
- [.editorconfig](mdc:.editorconfig): Editor configuration
- [commitlint.config.js](mdc:commitlint.config.js): Commit message linting configuration
